---
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us | DragonFruit"
  description="The short story behind DragonFruit, a workspace for people who think across fields and build with agents."
  canonicalPath="/about"
>
  <main class="essay-shell about-main">
    <div class="about-copy">
      <header class="home-header">
        <SiteHeader />
        <h1>Why DragonFruit exists.</h1>
      </header>

      <section class="home-section about-story">
        <p>
          DragonFruit started from a simple feeling: modern work has too many rooms. Notes live in one place, tasks in
          another, context in chat, and the actual thinking gets squeezed between tools.
        </p>
        <p>
          We wanted a workspace for people who move across subjects. Designers who write. Engineers who research.
          Founders who need to think before they decide. Small teams who want agents to help without turning the work
          into noise.
        </p>
        <p>
          The app is built around that shape of work. Documents, tasks, and agents should sit close together, so a rough
          idea can become a plan, a plan can become a draft, and a draft can become something real.
        </p>
        <p>DragonFruit is for making the next honest thing with a little more clarity.</p>
        <span class="cta-row"><span aria-hidden="true">→</span><a href="https://app.dragonfruit.sh">Start now for free</a></span>
      </section>

      <footer class="site-footer">
        <div class="legal-row">
          <a href="https://app.dragonfruit.sh/legal/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
          <a href="https://app.dragonfruit.sh/legal/terms">Terms and Conditions</a>
          <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} DragonFruit</span>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>

    <div class="about-illustration-wrap">
      <img
        class="about-illustration"
        src="/assets/essays-listing-illustration.png"
        alt="Renaissance-style rose engraving of a writer at a desk with books, notes, and a laptop"
        width="1536"
        height="1024"
      />
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
